PN,31501
SC,0001
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FChancellor Rachel Reeves claims Labour
OL,7,Fhas "restored economic stability"
OL,8,Fdespite downgraded growth forecasts
OL,9,Ffor 2026 and rising unemployment.
OL,11,FDelivering her spring statement to MPs
OL,12,Fin the House of Commons on Tuesday,
OL,13,FReeves said the government has "the
OL,14,Fright economic plan for our country",
OL,15,Fand that she believes families will
OL,16,Ffeel "better off" by the next election.
OL,18,FBut she also announced economic growth
OL,19,Fis forecast to slow in 2026, and
OL,20,Funemployment is set to peak later this
OL,21,Fyear.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FThe US-Israel war with Iran means that
OL,7,Fany narrow improvements in the economy
OL,8,Fand the Office for Budget
OL,9,FResponsibility's forecasts are likely
OL,10,Fto be overturned, with a spike in oil
OL,11,Fand gas prices likely to lead to
OL,12,Fhigher inflation and energy prices.
OL,14,FReeves addressed the conflict in the
OL,15,FMiddle East at the start of her
OL,16,Fspeech, saying: "It is incumbent on me
OL,17,Fand on this government to chart a
OL,18,Fcourse through that uncertainty to
OL,19,Fsecure our economy against shocks. And
OL,20,Fprotect families from the turbulence
OL,21,Fthat we see beyond our borders."
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FThe OBR said in their forecast
OL,7,Fpublished on Tuesday that "significant
OL,8,Frisks, including from conflict in the
OL,9,FMiddle East, mean outcomes both
OL,10,Fsubstantially above and below this
OL,11,Fforecast are possible."
OL,13,FThe spring statement is a chance for
OL,14,FReeves to update MPs on the state of
OL,15,Fthe economy, as she responds to
OL,16,Findependent forecasts from the OBR.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31504
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FThose forecasts published on Tuesday
OL,7,Fshow GDP is projected to rise more
OL,8,Fslowly than expected in 2026, and then
OL,9,Fto grow slightly faster after that,
OL,10,Fwith an increase of 1.1% in 2026 and
OL,11,Fan average increase of 1.6% a year
OL,12,Funtil 2030.
OL,14,FWhile unemployment is set to peak
OL,15,Flater this year and then fall every
OL,16,Fyear until 2030, ending at 4.1%, which
OL,17,Fis lower than it was at the start of
OL,18,Fthe Parliament.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31505
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,F"I am not satisfied with these
OL,7,Fforecasts," Reeves told the Commons,
OL,8,Fblaming sluggish growth on "deep
OL,9,Feconomic scars by the party opposite
OL,10,Fand their mates in Reform."
OL,12,FShadow Chancellor Sir Mel Stride
OL,13,Fbranded the spring statement a
OL,14,F"surrender statement" and accused the
OL,15,Fgovernment of giving up on the British
OL,16,Fpeople.
OL,18,FHe asked: "Is that it? What utter
OL,19,Fcomplacency, a Chancellor in denial.
OL,20,FShe speaks of stability. What planet
OL,21,Fis she on?
OL,26,@vD@AOUvD@UO]zD@KOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,F"She has lurched from putting up taxes
OL,7,Fto destroying growth, to destroying
OL,8,Fheadroom, to coming back to putting up
OL,9,Fmore taxes, more growth destroyed.
OL,10,FRound and round we go, like a fiscal
OL,11,Ftwister ripping up everything in its
OL,12,Fpath."
OL,14,FWhile this year's spring statement did
OL,15,Fnot contain any policy or tax and
OL,16,Fspend changes, it's significant
OL,17,Fbecause it's one of only two set-piece
OL,18,Fmoments in the year where the
OL,19,Fchancellor addresses MPs on the state
OL,20,Fof the economy.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FThe spring statement is not a Budget,
OL,7,Fbut more of a mid-year update on the
OL,8,Fpublic finances, after the Labour
OL,9,Fgovernment decided they would only
OL,10,Fhave one "fiscal event" a year.
OL,12,FThe government published the OBR
OL,13,Fforecast itself this year after the
OL,14,Fwatchdog accidentally published the
OL,15,FAutumn Budget early.
OL,17,FSubscribe free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31508
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FThe chancellor pointed to falling
OL,7,Finflation and interest rate cuts as
OL,8,Fsuccesses that have resulted in an
OL,9,Feasing of living pressures, although
OL,10,Feconomic growth has been sluggish.
OL,12,FGDP figures released in February
OL,13,Fshowed the economy grew by only 0.1%
OL,14,Fin the last three months of 2025,
OL,15,Fwhich was less than expected, while
OL,16,Funemployment in the UK rose to its
OL,17,Fhighest rate in nearly five years at
OL,18,Fthe end of 2025.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31509
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FThe Bank of England cut interest rates
OL,7,Fin December, while inflation has been
OL,8,Ffalling, retail sales are improving,
OL,9,Fand the government got a record
OL,10,Fsurplus from tax receipts in January.
OL,12,FPolling by More in Common released on
OL,13,FTuesday shows the rise in unemployment
OL,14,Fhas had much greater cut through and
OL,15,Fnegative reaction than falls in
OL,16,Fborrowing and inflation.
OL,18,F59% of Brits say they don't expect the
OL,19,Fcost of living crisis to ever end,
OL,20,Fwhile only 19% of people know that
OL,21,Finflation has fallen in recent months.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31510
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1772586178
OL,3,CSpring statement: UK growth to slow
OL,4,Cand unemployment set to rise in 2026
OL,6,FAsked on Tuesday if there was any
OL,7,Fpoint in doing a spring statement when
OL,8,Fthe global economy has just been
OL,9,Fupended, Chief Secretary to the Prime
OL,10,FMinister Darren Jones insisted:
OL,11,F"Because of what's going on in the
OL,12,Fworld, our plan to make Britain
OL,13,Fstronger and more resilient at home is
OL,14,Fthe right plan."
OL,16,FHave you heard our podcast Talking
OL,17,FPolitics? Tom and Robert dig into the
OL,18,Fbiggest issues dominating the
OL,19,Fpolitical agenda in every episode...
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                   G10/10
